The remarkable life story of eighties pop icon Adam Ant including his poverty stricken childhood, the mental health problems that led to him being forced into a psychiatric hospital and the pressures of international stardom. Also, Ed Casabian, the New York City Nomad explains why he's happy to stay in a different house with different people, every week Show less